<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The incidence and prevalence
of urethral strictures in men in Russia are not precisely known.&nbsp;In the
United States, the incidence of this disease was 274 cases per 100 thousand of
all medical requests.&nbsp;The incidence of urethral stricture increases with
age and is 0.6% between the ages of 65 and 69 years and 1.9% after 85
years.&nbsp;Urethral stricture in women is rare and usually occurs as a result
of trauma during childbirth or intercourse, as well as after some gynecological
diseases.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
